      "description": "This 996-generation Carrera 4S represents the pinnacle of the naturally aspirated M96 flat-six, featuring VarioCam Plus valve timing for an optimized power band. The widebody chassis provides increased torsional rigidity and houses the sophisticated all-wheel-drive system with a viscous clutch center differential. This example features a precise 6-speed manual transaxle with a factory-optioned short-throw shifter. The suspension geometry remains laser-straight, riding on original hollow-spoke wheels with four-piston monoblock Brembo calipers biting into ventilated, cross-drilled rotors. Every bushing is pliable, and the engine exhibits zero bore scoring or IMS issues, with documented oil analysis confirming peak internal health and optimal compression across all cylinders.",
